<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-29T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="418" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 815.156/2</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EJ1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Ewing</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-29T18:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 29, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Mr. <persName>Casey</persName>, of W. R. Grace &amp; Co., has been
                                authorized by Mr. <persName>Rosseter</persName>, of the Pacific
                                Mail, to sound the Government of Honduras regarding development of
                                the port at San Lorenzo. <persName>Casey</persName> should leave
                                Salvador in October, spending the 4th and 5th at Tegucigalpa.
                                Believe he wants port concession on Sacate Grande Island.</p>
                            <p>In view of conditions, Department desires you to use every possible
                                proper effort to advance interests of American commerce.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>